<p>The form below is a password box, that requires you to select a Strong Password. For the purposes of this test, a strong password has the following rules:
	<ul>
		<li>At least one capital letter</li>
		<li>At least one lower case letter</li>
		<li>At least one number</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<p>Write code to validate the form. If the text in the box does not meet the criteria, the form should <strong>NOT</strong> submit, and an alert should pop up telling the user their password is not strong enough.</p>

<div class="question">
	<form>
		<label class="pw">Create a strong password:</label><br>
		<input type="text" id="pwBox" name="password" placeholder="Password..."><br>
		<input type="submit" value="Create Password">
	</form>
</div>

<script>
	$(function() {
		/**** YOU MAY MODIFY THE CODE BELOW ****/
		$('input:submit').on('click', function() {
			var password = $('input#pwBox:text').val();
			if (notStrong(password)) {
				return false;
			};
		});

		function notStrong(password) {
			var full_string = password.match(/(?=.*\d)(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])/);
			if (!full_string) {
				alert("Your password is not strong enough!");
				return true;
			};
			return false;
		};
		/**** STOP MODIFYING HERE. ****/
	});
</script>
